#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:139
msgid "Recommended auto-detected flow:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:141
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --model-path Qwen/Qwen-Image \\\n"
"  --transformer-weights-path /path/to/svdq-int4_r32-qwen-image.safetensors "
"\\\n"
"  --prompt \"a beautiful sunset\" \\\n"
"  --save-output\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:149
msgid "Manual override when the filename does not encode the quant settings:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:151
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --model-path Qwen/Qwen-Image \\\n"
"  --transformer-weights-path /path/to/custom_nunchaku_checkpoint.safetensors "
"\\\n"
"  --enable-svdquant \\\n"
"  --quantization-precision int4 \\\n"
"  --quantization-rank 128 \\\n"
"  --prompt \"a beautiful sunset\" \\\n"
"  --save-output\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:164
msgid ""
"`--transformer-weights-path` is the canonical flag for Nunchaku checkpoints. "
"Older config names such as `quantized_model_path` are treated as "
"compatibility aliases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:167
msgid ""
"Auto-detection only happens when the checkpoint basename matches `svdq-(int4|"
"fp4)_r{rank}`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:169
msgid ""
"The CLI values are `int4` and `nvfp4`. In filenames, the NVFP4 variant is "
"written as `fp4`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:171
msgid ""
"Lightning checkpoints usually expect matching `--num-inference-steps`, such "
"as `4` or `8`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:173
msgid ""
"Current runtime validation only allows Nunchaku on NVIDIA CUDA Ampere (SM8x) "
"or SM12x GPUs. Hopper (SM90) is currently rejected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:176
msgid "[ModelSlim](https://gitcode.com/Ascend/msmodelslim)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:177
msgid ""
"MindStudio-ModelSlim (msModelSlim) is a model offline quantization "
"compression tool launched by MindStudio and optimized for Ascend hardware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:179
msgid "**Installation**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:181
msgid ""
"# Clone repo and install msmodelslim:\n"
"git clone https://gitcode.com/Ascend/msmodelslim.git\n"
"cd msmodelslim\n"
"bash install.sh\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:188
msgid "**Multimodal_sd quantization**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:190
msgid ""
"Download the original floating-point weights of the large model. Taking "
"Wan2.2-T2V-A14B as an example, you can go to [Wan2.2-T2V-A14B](https://"
"modelscope.cn/models/Wan-AI/Wan2.2-T2V-A14B) to obtain the original model "
"weights. Then install other dependencies (related to the model, refer to the "
"modelscope model card)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:191
msgid ""
"Note: You can find pre-quantized validated models on [modelscope/Eco-Tech]"
"(https://modelscope.cn/models/Eco-Tech)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:193
msgid "Run quantization using one-click quantization (recommended):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:195
msgid ""
"msmodelslim quant \\\n"
"  --model_path /path/to/wan2_2_float_weights \\\n"
"  --save_path /path/to/wan2_2_quantized_weights \\\n"
"  --device npu \\\n"
"  --model_type Wan2_2 \\\n"
"  --quant_type w8a8 \\\n"
"  --trust_remote_code True\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:205
msgid ""
"For more detailed examples of quantization of models, as well as information "
"about their support, see the [examples](https://gitcode.com/Ascend/"
"msmodelslim/blob/master/example/multimodal_sd/README.md) section in "
"ModelSLim repo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:207
msgid ""
"Note: SGLang does not support quantized embeddings, please disable this "
"option when quantizing using msmodelslim."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:209
msgid "**Auto-Detection and different formats**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:211
msgid ""
"For msmodelslim checkpoints, it's enough to specify only ```--model-path```, "
"the detection of quantization occurs automatically for each layer using "
"parsing of      `quant_model_description.json` config."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:213
msgid ""
"In the case of `Wan2.2` only `Diffusers` weights storage format are "
"supported, whereas modelslim saves the quantized model in the original "
"`Wan2.2` format,   for conversion in use `python/sglang/multimodal_gen/tools/"
"wan_repack.py` script:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:216
msgid ""
"python wan_repack.py \\\n"
"  --input-path {path_to_quantized_model} \\\n"
"  --output-path {path_to_converted_model}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:222
msgid ""
"After that, please copy all files from original `Diffusers` checkpoint "
"(instead of `transformer`/`tranfsormer_2` folders)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:224
msgid "**Usage Example**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:226
msgid "With auto-detected flow:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/quantization.md:228
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --model-path Eco-Tech/Wan2.2-T2V-A14B-Diffusers-w8a8 \\\n"
"  --prompt \"a beautiful sunset\" \\\n"
"  --save-output\n"
msgstr ""

